(3) Mancipatio: res mancipi (viz. land aad rustic servitudes in Italy, slaveS, domestic beasts of burden, free persons in potestas, manus or mancipium, and under certain circutu- stances a man’s whole property in the aggregate (familia)) could be con· veyed in full ownership only by this or in iure cessio ; it is described by Gaius i. 119-122.
